.TH GMT\-MAIL 1 "2026-03-18" "gmt-mail dev" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gmt\-mail \- send personalized emails in bulk using a template and a configuration file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gmt\-mail
.RB [ \-dry\-run ]
.B \-config\-path
.I file
.B \-template\-path
.I file
.br
.B gmt\-mail
.B \-sample\-config
.br
.B gmt\-mail
.B \-sample\-template
.br
.B gmt\-mail
.B \-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gmt\-mail
(Go Mailing Tool) sends personalized emails in bulk.
It reads a list of recipients and mail metadata from an INI configuration file,
substitutes per-recipient variables into an email template, and sends the
resulting messages via SMTP with mandatory TLS encryption.
.PP
In dry-run mode, emails are printed to standard output instead of being sent,
allowing review before committing to delivery.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-config\-path " file"
Path to the INI configuration file. Required unless using
.BR \-sample\-config ,
.BR \-sample\-template ,
or
.BR \-version .
.TP
.BI \-template\-path " file"
Path to the email template file. Required unless using
.BR \-sample\-config ,
.BR \-sample\-template ,
or
.BR \-version .
.TP
.B \-dry\-run
Preview all emails on standard output without connecting to an SMTP server.
SMTP credentials are not required in this mode.
.TP
.B \-sample\-config
Print a sample configuration file to standard output and exit.
.TP
.B \-sample\-template
Print a sample email template to standard output and exit.
.TP
.B \-version
Print the version string and exit.
.TP
.B \-h
Print a brief usage message and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
The configuration file uses INI format with two required sections.
Key names are case-insensitive.
.SS [general]
.TP
.B From
Sender name and email address for the mail header.
Example:
.IR "\(dqFrodo Baggins\(dq <frodo@shire.org>" .
Required.
.TP
.B subject
Email subject line. May contain template variables (see
.BR "TEMPLATE VARIABLES" ).
Required.
.TP
.B Cc
Comma-separated CC addresses. Optional.
.TP
.B Reply\-To
Reply-To address. Optional.
.TP
.B attachments
Comma-separated file paths to attach to every email.
Files are verified at configuration parse time.
Optional.
.SS [recipients]
Each line defines one recipient in the form:
.PP
.RS
.IR email = "First Last" | KEY :- VALUE | KEY :- VALUE |...
.RE
.PP
The first word after
.B =
is the first name; subsequent words up to the first
.B |
form the last name. Key-value pairs after
.B |
use
.B :\-
as the separator. Keys are converted to uppercase for template matching.
.PP
.B Per-recipient overrides:
.TP
.BI Cc:\- addr1,addr2
Replace the global Cc list for this recipient.
.TP
.BI Cc:\-+ addr1,addr2
Append to the global Cc list for this recipient.
.TP
.BI As:\- file1,file2
Replace the global attachments for this recipient.
.TP
.BI As:\-+ file1
Append to the global attachments for this recipient.
.SH TEMPLATE VARIABLES
The following placeholders are substituted in both the subject line and the
template body:
.TP
.B %FN%
Recipient's first name.
.TP
.B %LN%
Recipient's last name.
.TP
.B %EA%
Recipient's email address.
.TP
.BI % KEY %
Any custom key defined in the recipient's data (uppercase).
.PP
Unresolved placeholders are left as-is in the output and a warning is logged
for each one.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
SMTP credentials are loaded from environment variables.
If a
.B .env
file exists in the working directory, it is loaded automatically (environment
variables take precedence over
.B .env
values).
.TP
.B SMTP_HOST
SMTP server hostname (e.g.,
.IR smtp.gmail.com ).
.TP
.B SMTP_PORT
SMTP server port (e.g.,
.IR 587 ).
.TP
.B SENDER_EMAIL
Email address used for SMTP authentication.
.TP
.B SENDER_PASSWORD
Password for SMTP authentication.
.PP
All four variables are required when sending email.
They are not required for
.BR \-dry\-run ,
.BR \-sample\-config ,
.BR \-sample\-template ,
or
.BR \-version .
.PP
All SMTP connections use mandatory TLS; credentials are never transmitted in
plaintext.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success. All emails sent or dry-run completed.
.TP
.B 1
Usage error. Missing required flags.
.TP
.B 2
Configuration or template file error (missing, unreadable, invalid, or
no recipients found).
.TP
.B 3
SMTP connection error (missing or invalid credentials, connection failure).
.TP
.B 4
Partial failure. One or more emails failed to send.
.SH EXAMPLES
Generate sample files to get started:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gmt\-mail \-sample\-config > config.ini
gmt\-mail \-sample\-template > template.eml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set up SMTP credentials:
.PP
.RS
.nf
cp .env.example .env
vi .env
.fi
.RE
.PP
Preview emails without sending:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gmt\-mail \-dry\-run \-config\-path config.ini \-template\-path template.eml
.fi
.RE
.PP
Send emails:
.PP
.RS
.nf
gmt\-mail \-config\-path config.ini \-template\-path template.eml
.fi
.RE
